    "context": "Hong Kong bakeries (餅店) are a blend of Chinese and Western influences. Pineapple buns (菠蘿包) are arguably HK's most iconic pastry — despite the name, there's no pineapple in them. Wife cakes (老婆餅) are a sweet flaky pastry with winter melon filling.",
    "cultural_note": "The pineapple bun (菠蘿包, bo1 lo4 baau1) has no pineapple in it. The cracked golden crust just happens to look like pineapple skin. Split while hot and stuffed with a thick slab of cold butter, its making technique was added to Hong Kong's first Intangible Cultural Heritage Inventory in 2014, alongside milk tea and the egg tart.",
